{
  "answer": "**Manusmṛti 4.138** provides the following specific rule on speech for a Brahmana householder (a *snātaka*):\n\n> One should speak the truth, one should speak what is pleasant; one should not speak an unpleasant truth. One should not speak a pleasant untruth; this is the eternal Dharma.[^1]\n\nThis verse outlines the balance between truthfulness (*satya*) and pleasantness (*priya*), prioritizing Dharma by avoiding both harsh truths and flattering lies.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Manusmṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/04/translation/#p-133ce4).\n\n[^2]: Manusmṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/04/translation/#p-133ce4).",
